t: Psalm 105
O*p give thanks unto the Lord;*s call upon his name: make known his deeds among the people.
Sing*p unto him, sing psalms unto him: talk ye of all his wondrous works.
Glory*p ye in his holy name: let the heart of them rejoice that seek the Lord.*s
Seek*p the Lord,*s and his strength: seek his face evermore.
Remember*p his marvellous works that he hath done; his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth;
O*p ye seed of Abraham his servant, ye children of Jacob his chosen.
He*p is the Lord*s our God: his judgments are in all the earth.
He*p hath remembered his covenant for ever, the word which he commanded to a thousand generations.
Which*p covenant he made with Abraham, and his oath unto Isaac;
And*p confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law, and to Israel for an everlasting covenant:
Saying,*p Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan, the lot of your inheritance:
When*p they were but a few men in number; yea, very few, and strangers in it.
When*p they went from one nation to another, from one kingdom to another people;
He*p suffered no man to do them wrong: yea, he reproved kings for their sakes;
Saying,*p Touch not mine anointed, and do my prophets no harm.
Moreover*p he called for a famine upon the land: he brake the whole staff of bread.
He*p sent a man before them, even Joseph, who was sold for a servant:
Whose*p feet they hurt with fetters: he was laid in iron:
Until*p the time that his word came: the word of the Lord*s tried him.
The*p king sent and loosed him; even the ruler of the people, and let him go free.
He*p made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his substance:
To*p bind his princes at his pleasure; and teach his senators wisdom.
Israel*p also came into Egypt; and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.
And*p he increased his people greatly; and made them stronger than their enemies.
He*p turned their heart to hate his people, to deal subtilly with his servants.
He*p sent Moses his servant; and Aaron whom he had chosen.
They*p shewed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.
He*p sent darkness, and made it dark; and they rebelled not against his word.
He*p turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.
Their*p land brought forth frogs in abundance, in the chambers of their kings.
He*p spake, and there came divers sorts of flies, and lice in all their coasts.
He*p gave them hail for rain, and flaming fire in their land.
He*p smote their vines also and their fig trees; and brake the trees of their coasts.
He*p spake, and the locusts came, and caterpillers, and that without number,
And*p did eat up all the herbs in their land, and devoured the fruit of their ground.
He*p smote also all the firstborn in their land, the chief of all their strength.
He*p brought them forth also with silver and gold: and there was not one feeble person among their tribes.
Egypt*p was glad when they departed: for the fear of them fell upon them.
He*p spread a cloud for a covering; and fire to give light in the night.
The*p people asked, and he brought quails, and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.
He*p opened the rock, and the waters gushed out; they ran in the dry places like a river.
For*p he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham his servant.
And*p he brought forth his people with joy, and his chosen with gladness:
And*p gave them the lands of the heathen: and they inherited the labour of the people;
That*p they might observe his statutes, and keep his laws. Praise ye the Lord.*s
